                <head>173. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 21 the National Security Council issued a revised version of <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5805/1, “U.S. Policy Toward Yugoslavia.” In a
                    November 23 memorandum accompanying the revised text, <persName
                        corresp="#p_LJS1">James S. Lay</persName>, Executive Secretary of the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>, noted that the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> Planning Board decided that “only revisions of an editorial
                    nature were necessary to bring this policy up to date.” A copy of the revised
                    version of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5805/1 is in Department of State,
                        <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    Files: Lot 62 D1, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5805. Regarding <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5805/1, see <ref target="#d120">Documents
                        120</ref> and <ref target="#d122">122</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
